        "description": {
            "value": "<p>Sigils and runes of ancient and powerful magic cover the iron cladding on this long wooden staff. A <em>staff of the magi</em> is a <em>+3 major striking staff</em>, and when wielding it you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to saving throws against spells.</p>\n<p>Voluntarily destroying a <em>staff of the magi</em> unleashes a truly devastating wave of arcane energy that surges out, dissipating with distance. When wielding the staff, you can break it using an Interact action. This releases a @Template[burst|distance:30] magical explosion centered on the staff. This deals @Damage[2d10[force]] damage per charge remaining in the staff (@Check[reflex|dc:40|basic]). You automatically critically fail your save. The explosion continues to echo beyond the initial blast zone, dealing half as much damage to creatures beyond 30 feet but within a @Template[burst|distance:60]. A creature reduced to 0 Hit Points by this damage dies instantly; this is a death effect.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Craft Requirements</strong> Supply one casting of all listed levels of all listed spells.</p>"
        },
